title: AttributeError: module 'tensorflow.python.training.checkpointable' has no attribute 'CheckpointableBase'
body:
Hello, really thank you for your time. I am not a professional programmer and I am trying to install deeplabcut for my behavioral analysis. 

I use Windows10 and run deeplabcut2.x with an Anaconda Env. However, when I use ipython to import deeplabcut, I got the attribute Error which I don't know how to solve.
